    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIf we open a float window with the default `zindex` (`50`) and want to close it with `:fclose`, first we need to close (enough quickly, rather by keymap ;) ) all four extui windows if present. All those windows are (usually) hidden but have `zindex` near to `200` so `:fc` starts from them.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\ninit.lua:\n```lua\nrequire('vim._extui').enable({enable = true, msg = {target = 'msg'}})\nlocal buf = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\nvim.api.nvim_open_win(buf, false, {\n  relative = 'editor',\n  width = 20,\n  height = 2,\n  row = 0.9,\n  col = 0.9,\n  border = 'rounded',\n  style = 'minimal',\n})\n```\n\n- `nvim --clean -u init.lua`\n- try `:fc` several times\n- look at `:=vim.iter(vim.api.nvim_list_wins()):each(function(win) local cfg = vim.api.nvim_win_get_config(win); print(('%s: {zindex: %s, hide: %s}'):format(win, cfg.zindex, cfg.hide)) end)` output\n- define `:nmap <Esc> <Cmd>fc<CR>` and repeat pressing `<Esc>` frequently\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`:fclose` does not affect hidden windows.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-1407+gfafc329bbd\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDebian Sid\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacrity\n\n### Installation\n\nfrom repo",
    "closed_at": null,
